P_{ext} & =\int d\Omega\,\mathbf{S}_{ext}\cdot\mathbf{u}_{r}=\frac{1}{2Z}\textrm{Re}\left\{ \int d\Omega\,\left(-\mathbf{E}_{s}\times\mathbf{H}_{i}^{*}-\mathbf{E}_{i}\times\mathbf{H}_{s}^{*}\right)\cdot\mathbf{u}_{r}\right\} =\nonumber \\
 & =\frac{2\pi}{Zk^{2}}\sum_{n}\textrm{Im}\left\{ \left(\alpha_{E}^{(n)}\left(\mathbf{E}_{n}\cdot\mathbf{E}_{0}^{*}\right)+\alpha_{M}^{(n)}\left(\mathbf{H}_{n}\cdot\mathbf{H}_{0}^{*}\right)\right)e^{-ik\mathbf{r}_{n}\cdot\mathbf{u}_{k}}\right\} =\label{ext_150}\\
 & =\frac{2\pi}{Zk^{2}}\sum_{n}\textrm{Im}\left\{ \left(\alpha_{E}^{(n)}\left(\mathbf{E}_{n}\cdot\mathbf{E}_{0}^{*}\left(\mathbf{r}_{n}\right)\right)+\alpha_{M}^{(n)}\left(\mathbf{H}_{n}\cdot\mathbf{H}_{0}^{*}\left(\mathbf{r}_{n}\right)\right)\right)\right\} 
\end{align}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Notice that in the case of a single particle, 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{E}_{1}=\mathbf{E}_{0}e^{ik\mathbf{r}_{1}\cdot\mathbf{u}_{k}}$
\end_inset

, and hence the phase cancels.
 In fact the solution is invariant under a translation of the whole system
 because the exciting fields 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{E}_{n}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{H}_{n}$
\end_inset

 are proportional to the phase of the field, this phase if canceled by the
 conjugate of the incoming external field appearing in the above equation
 .
 Explicitly, for a single particle we have.
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
P_{ext}=\frac{2\pi}{Zk^{2}}\textrm{Im}\left\{ \alpha_{E}^{(n)}\left|\mathbf{E}_{0}\right|^{2}+\alpha_{M}^{(n)}\left|\mathbf{H}_{0}\right|^{2}\right\} \label{ext_160}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Notice also that the terms proportional to 
\begin_inset Formula $\exp\left(\pm2ikr\right)$
\end_inset

 do not enter in the final result because the total contribution has the
 form 
\begin_inset Formula $\textrm{Re}\left(z-z^{*}\right)=0$
\end_inset

.
 On the contrary, the terms without the phase 
\begin_inset Formula $\exp\left(\pm2ikr\right)$
\end_inset

 contribute in the form 
\begin_inset Formula $\textrm{Re}\left(z+z^{*}\right)\ne0$
\end_inset

 in general.
\end_layout

